:R-HSA-2029481  a           owl:NamedIndividual , obo:GO_0008150 ;
        rdfs:comment        "Cross-linking of FCGRs with IgG coated immune complexes results in tyrosine phosphorylation of the immuno tyrosine activation motif (ITAMs) of the rececptor by membrane-bound tyrosine kinases of the SRC family. The phosphorylated ITAM tyrosines serve as docking sites for Src homology 2 (SH2) domain-containing SYK kinase. Recruitment and activation of SYK is critical for FCGR-mediated signaling in phagocytosis, but the exact role of SYK in this process is unclear. Activated SYK then transmits downstream signals leading to actin polymerization and particle internalization." ;
        rdfs:label          "FCGR activation" ;
        dc:contributor      "GOC:reactome_curators" , "Edited: Garapati, P V, 2012-01-04" , "Authored: Garapati, P V, 2012-01-04" , "Reviewed: Rosales, C, 2012-05-14" ;
        dc:date             "2026-06-29" ;
        pav:providedBy      "https://reactome.org" ;
        oboInOwl:hasDbXref  "R-HSA-2029481" ;
        skos:narrower       <http://model.geneontology.org/R-HSA-2029480/R-HSA-2029480> ;
        skos:note           "org.biopax.paxtools.model.level3.Pathway" .

